# Next.js Rules

## Router Choice

- Use the **App Router** (`app/`) for all new projects (Next.js 13+).
- Keep the Pages Router (`pages/`) only in legacy projects; do not mix the two routers in the same project.

## Server vs. Client Components

- Components in the `app/` directory are **Server Components by default** — keep them server-side unless interactivity is required.
- Add `"use client"` only when a component needs browser APIs, React hooks, or event listeners.
- Keep `"use client"` boundaries as **deep in the tree as possible** to maximise server rendering.
- Never import a Client Component into a Server Component without a boundary; pass server data as props instead.

## Data Fetching

- Fetch data directly inside Server Components using `async/await`; avoid `useEffect` for initial data loading.
- Use `fetch` with Next.js cache options (`cache: 'force-cache'`, `next: { revalidate: N }`) instead of manual caching layers.
- Use `React.cache` to deduplicate fetch calls across the same request.
- Prefer **React Server Actions** for form mutations; avoid separate API routes for simple CRUD operations.

## Routing & Navigation

- Use the `<Link>` component from `next/link` for all internal navigation — never use `<a>` tags directly.
- Use `useRouter` (from `next/navigation` in App Router) only for programmatic navigation.
- Use dynamic segments (`[slug]`, `[...slug]`) and generate static params with `generateStaticParams`.
- Co-locate `loading.tsx`, `error.tsx`, and `not-found.tsx` with their route segments.

## Layouts & Templates

- Use `layout.tsx` for persistent UI (nav, sidebars) that should not re-mount on navigation.
- Use `template.tsx` when you need a fresh instance of the component on each navigation.
- Share root metadata in the root `layout.tsx`; override per route with `generateMetadata`.

## Images & Fonts

- Always use `next/image` for images; supply `width`, `height`, and meaningful `alt` text.
- Use `next/font` to load fonts — it eliminates external network requests and prevents layout shift.

## Metadata & SEO

- Export a `metadata` object or a `generateMetadata` function from every `page.tsx`.
- Include `title`, `description`, and Open Graph tags at minimum.

## API Routes (Route Handlers)

- Place route handlers in `app/api/.../route.ts` following REST conventions.
- Export named functions matching HTTP verbs (`GET`, `POST`, `PUT`, `PATCH`, `DELETE`).
- Return `NextResponse` objects with explicit status codes and typed JSON bodies.
- Validate and sanitise all incoming request data before processing.

## Environment Variables

- Prefix public variables with `NEXT_PUBLIC_`; keep secrets server-side only.
- Never access `process.env` inside Client Components.
- Document all required env vars in `.env.example`.

## Performance

- Enable **Partial Prerendering (PPR)** for pages that mix static and dynamic content (Next.js 14+).
- Use `React.lazy` / dynamic imports (`next/dynamic`) with `{ ssr: false }` for heavy client-only libraries.
- Avoid large third-party scripts; load them via `next/script` with the appropriate `strategy`.

## File & Folder Structure

```
app/
  (group)/             # Route groups (no URL segment)
  [param]/             # Dynamic routes
  layout.tsx
  page.tsx
  loading.tsx
  error.tsx
components/            # Shared UI components
lib/                   # Utilities, helpers, server-side logic
actions/               # Server Actions
hooks/                 # Custom client hooks
types/
public/
```

## Testing

- Use **Vitest** or **Jest** with React Testing Library for unit/component tests.
- Use **Playwright** or **Cypress** for end-to-end tests against a running Next.js dev or preview build.
- Mock `next/navigation` hooks in unit tests.
